{"parse":{"title":"earphone","pageid":455939,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n{{wp}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{compound|en|ear|phone}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈɪə(ɹ)fəʊn/}}\n* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-earphone.wav|a=Southern England}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# A [[transducer]] that converts [[electric]] [[signal]]s into [[sound]] and is held near the [[ear]], especially as part of a [[telephone]]; an [[earpiece]] or [[headphone]].\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|earphoned\n}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|en|headphone}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top-see|sound device held near the ear|earbud}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|kufje|f}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|سَمَّاعَة|f}}, {{t|ar|سَمَاعَات الرَّأْس|f-p}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{t|aii|ܫܡܘܥܬܐ|f|tr=šāmōˁtā}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|ականջակալ}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t|az|qulaqlıq}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|наву́шнікі|m-p}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|слу́шалки|f-p}}\n* Burmese: {{t+|my|နားကြပ်}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|auricular}}\n* Chichewa: {{t|ny|mahedifoni}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|耳機|tr=ěrjī}}, {{t|cmn|耳筒|tr=ěrtǒng}}\n* Czech: {{t|cs|sluchátka|n-p}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|hovedtelefoner}}, {{t|da|øretelefon|c}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|oortelefoon}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|kapaŭskultiloj}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|kõrvaklapid}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|kuuloke}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|écouteur|m}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|ყურსასმენი}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Ohrhörer|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|ακουστικό|n}}\n* Gujarati: {{t|gu|કાનદટ્ટો}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|אוזניות|alt=אָזְנִית / אוזניות}}\n* Hindi: {{t|hi|हेडफ़ोन|m}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|fülhallgató}}\n* Indonesian: {{t|id|penyuara kuping}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|cluasán|m}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|auricolare|m}}, {{t+|it|cuffia|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|イヤフォン|tr=iyafon}}, {{t+|ja|イヤホン|tr=iyahon}}\n* Kazakh: {{t|kk|құлаққап}}\n* Khmer: {{t|km|កាសស្ដាប់ត្រចៀក|tr=kaah sdap trɑɑciək}}\n* Korean: {{t|ko|이어폰}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{t|ky|кулаккап}}\n* Lao: {{t|lo|ຫູຟັງ}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|auscultābulum|n}} {{q|New Latin}}, {{t|la|concha auditoria|f}} {{q|New Latin}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|слушалки|f-p}}\n* Malay: {{t+|ms|fon kepala}}\n* Malayalam: {{t|ml|ഇയർഫോൺ}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|pokotaringa}}\n* Mongolian: {{t+|mn|чихэвч}}\n* Norwegian: {{t|no|hodetelefoner}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t|nn|hovudtelefon}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|هدفون|tr=hedfon}}\n* Polish: {{t|pl|[[słuchawka|słuchawki]]|nv-p}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|fone|m}}, {{t+|pt|fone de ouvido|m}}, {{t+|pt|auricular|m}}\n* Punjabi: {{t|pa|ਹੈਡਫ਼ੋਨਸ}}\n* Quechua: {{t|qu|rinri uyarina}}\n* Romanian: {{t|ro|căști audio}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|нау́шники|m-p}}, {{t|ru|[[головно́й]] [[телефо́н]]|m}}\n* Scots: {{t|sco|heidphones}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|fòn-cluaise|m}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|слушалице|f-p}}\n*: Latin: {{t|sh|slušalice|f-p}}\n* Sinhalese: {{t|si|හෙඩ්ෆෝන්}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|slúchadlá|n-p}}\n* Slovene: {{t|sl|slušalke|f-p}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Upper Sorbian: {{t|hsb|słuchatko|n}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|auricular|m}}, {{t|es|[[audífono]] [[intraaural]]|m}}, {{t|es|intraauricular|m}}, {{t|es|pinganillo|m}} {{q|wireless|stealthy}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|hörlur|c}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|talinig}}\n* Tamil: {{t|ta|காதொலிப்பான்}}\n* Tatar: {{t|tt|колакчыннар}}\n* Telugu: {{t|te|హెడ్‌ఫోన్స్}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|หูฟัง}}\n* Tibetan: {{t-needed|bo}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|kulaklık}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|наву́шники|m-p}}\n* Uzbek: {{t|uz|naushniklar}}, {{t|uz|minigarnituralar}}, {{t+|uz|quloqchin}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|ống nghe}}, {{t+|vi|tai nghe}}\n* Welsh: {{t|cy|clustffon|m}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|en|ear bud}}\n\n{{c|en|Sound}}"}}